   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Food Insecurity</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The United Nations estimates more than 725,000 in Lesotho, over a third of the
population do not have enough to eat. For two consecutive years flooding
followed by drought had resulted in the rapid rise of food prices for staple foods
due to poor harvest and in order to prevent the crisis escalating further, JOAC
awarded UNICEF GBP 30,000 and Action Aid GBP 24,000 to respond to the
emergency in areas of agricultural support, nutrition, health, water and
sanitation.</narrative>
  </description>
